text: Ali Maâloul (; born 1 January 1990) is a Tunisian football player who plays as a left back for Al Ahly and the Tunisia national team. He made his debut in the national team hopes April 9, 2011, against Malawi cash match for qualifying for the 2012 Olympics in London. Maâloul made his international debut for the Tunisia on 6 July 2013 against Morocco. He played his first African Cup in 2015, he participated also in 2017 Africa Cup of Nations. In June 2018 he was named in Tunisia’s 23-man squad for the 2018 FIFA World Cup in Russia. == References == Category:Living people Category:1990 births Category:Tunisian footballers Category:Sportspeople from Tunis Category:2022 FIFA World Cup players == Other websites == * * *
